items.name: +2 to All Saves vs Grapple or Shove

description.value: The slurk extrudes a slippery grease from its ventral glands to coat the floor under it and in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:5], turning the affected area into uneven ground for 10 minutes, after which it dries to a putrid crust. The DC to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.M76ycLAqHoAgbcej]{Balance} across the slime is @Check[type:acrobatics|dc:18|traits:action:balance,move].

A creature struck by a slurk's slime squirt becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.i3OJZU2nk64Df3xm]{Clumsy} and takes a -5-foot penalty to Speed for 1 hour or until the slime is removed.

The slime can be removed with a total of three Interact actions by the entangled creature or creatures adjacent to the creature. These actions don't need to be consecutive or made by the same creature.

@Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-effects.jQmfZcPD6xVYx5nb]{Effect: Entangling Slime}

You can ask questions of, receive answers from, and use the Diplomacy skill with animals. The spell doesn't make them more friendly than normal. Cunning animals are likely to be terse and evasive, while less intelligent ones often make inane comments.

You fill the minds of your enemies with doubt.

Enemies in the area must succeed at a Will save or take a -1 status penalty to attack rolls as long as they are in the area.

Once per turn, starting the turn after you cast bane, you can use a single action, which has the concentrate trait, to increase the emanation's radius by 5 feet and force enemies in the area that weren't yet affected to attempt another saving throw.

Bane can counteract bless.

@Compendium[pf2e.spell-effects.UTLp7omqsiC36bso]{Spell Effect: Bane}

The simplest magic does your bidding. You can perform simple magical effects for as long as you Sustain the Spell. Each time you Sustain the Spell, you can choose one of four options.

  • Cook Cool, warm, or flavor 1 pound of nonliving material.
  • Lift Slowly lift an unattended object of light Bulk or less 1 foot off the ground.
  • Make Create a temporary object of negligible Bulk, made of congealed magical substance. The object looks crude and artificial and is extremely fragile-it can't be used as a tool, weapon, or spell component.
  • Tidy Color, clean, or soil an object of light Bulk or less. You can affect an object of 1 Bulk with 10 rounds of concentration, and a larger object a 1 minute per Bulk.

Prestidigitation can't deal damage or cause adverse conditions. Any actual change to an object (beyond what is noted above) persists only as long as you Sustain the Spell.
These blades come in a variety of shapes and styles, but they are typically 2 feet long.
This thrown weapon is larger than an arrow but shorter than a javelin. It typically has a short shaft of wood ending in a metal tip and is sometimes stabilized by feathers or fur.
@Localize[PF2E.NPC.Abilities.Glossary.Darkvision]
@Localize[PF2E.NPC.Abilities.Glossary.Scent]

A mitflit's self-loathing makes it easy to influence. It takes a -4 penalty to its Will DC against checks to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.tHCqgwjtQtzNqVvd]{Coerce}, @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.2u915NdUyQan6uKF]{Demoralize}, @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.OX4fy22hQgUHDr0q]{Make an Impression}, and @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.DCb62iCBrJXy0Ik6]{Request}.

Mitflits can use Diplomacy to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.OX4fy22hQgUHDr0q]{Make an Impression} on and @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.DCb62iCBrJXy0Ik6]{Request} things of arthropods (insects, spiders, scorpions, crabs, and similar invertebrate animals). Most arthropods have a starting attitude of @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.fuG8dgthlDWfWjIA]{Indifferent} to mitflits.
@Localize[PF2E.NPC.Abilities.Glossary.AtWillSpells]
As long as it isn't @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened}, a mitflit gains a +2 status bonus to damage rolls against a creature that has previously damaged or tormented it.

@Localize[PF2E.NPC.Abilities.Glossary.AttackOfOpportunity]

[[/r {1d6+4}[bludgeoning]]]{1d6+4 bludgeoning damage}, @Check[type:fortitude|dc:20|basic:true]

@Localize[PF2E.NPC.Abilities.Glossary.Constrict]

Saving Throw @Check[type:fortitude|dc:18|basic:true]

Maximum Duration 6 rounds

Stage 1 [[/r {1d10}[poison]]]{1d10 poison damage} and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 1} (1 round)

Stage 2 [[/r {2d10}[poison]]]{2d10 poison damage} and enfeebled 1 (1 round)

Stage 3 [[/r {2d10}[poison]]]{2d10 poison damage} and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 2} (1 round)
@Localize[PF2E.NPC.Abilities.Glossary.Grab]

Trigger A living creature ends its turn in area A11 at night

Effect A ghastly image of Belcorra, seemingly composed of fresh blood, rises from the bloodstain on the floor and rotates in place like a lighthouse. Beams of cold blue light shine from Belcorra's eyes and open mouth, causing blisters and decay to spread across flesh. Living creatures within a @Template[type:burst|distance:30] from the center of area A11 must attempt a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:20|traits:damaging-effect] save.

The haunt then rolls initiative.

Critical Success The creature is unaffected.

Success The creature takes [[/r {1d8}[negative]]]{1d8 negative damage}.

Failure The creature takes [[/r {1d8+6}[negative]]]{1d8+6 negative damage} and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.TkIyaNPgTZFBCCuh]{Dazzled} for 1 round.

Critical Failure The creature takes [[/r {2d8+6}[negative]]]{2d8+6 negative damage} and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.XgEqL1kFApUbl5Z2]{Blinded} for 1 round then dazzled for 1 round.
